# RailsBase Docker Project 

This is a script to create a docker-fied Rails project

## Usage

```bash
1. Checkout this repo to some location
  i.e. Example Location: `cd ~ && git checkout https://github.com/hunli/rails_base.git`
2. Run the `create_service.sh` script and pass in desired path of new Rails project
  i.e. `~/rails_base/create_service.sh foo`

Result: A new Rails project will now be created at `~/foo`. There is a Makefile for
to make life easier.
i.e. `make enter`
```

